The paper discusses recent advances in AI and their applications in different domains, including national security. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI category. The paper also discusses the potential risks associated with the use of AI in a national security environment, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CR (security and privacy) category. The paper specifically mentions computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) as examples of multimedia applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.CV (computer vision) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of standards to enable trust in AI systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CL (computation and language) category.
